race.comment: MILES OF GLORY (4) won her maiden over this course and distance two runs back then tackled the Group 3 Reginald Allen last time and finished just 3.6 lengths from the promising Panova. If she holds that form this is her race to lose. SHOW BUSINESS (2) worked home strongly but missed by a whisker when resuming over 1100m at Hawkesbury last time out. Lightly raced mare better served over this slightly longer trip. Has plenty of improvement to come and is a definite threat. ME ME (3) returned from a six-month spell with a tough maiden win at this track and trip recently. Registered a career-high figure that day so she is making progress and can play a role in this tougher contest. PEWTER PEARL (5) has not appeared since winning her maiden over 900m at Newcastle in July, the only run of that prep. Likely improver following that run so don't write her off. The speedy MATCHSTICKS (7) has been competitive all prep and will give backers a sight again.
